# ============================================================
# Gitleaks Ignore File (.gitleaksignore)
# ============================================================
# This file contains fingerprints of false positive secrets
# that should not trigger gitleaks alerts.
#
# Format: Each line contains a SECRET FINGERPRINT, not a pattern.
# Fingerprints are obtained from gitleaks output when it detects
# a false positive secret.
#
# When gitleaks detects a secret, it outputs:
#   Fingerprint: <filename>:<ruleid>:<line-number>
#
# Copy the entire fingerprint line here to ignore that specific secret.
#
# Reference: https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks
# Docs: https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks#gitleaksignore

# ============================================================
# Example Format (replace with actual fingerprints)
# ============================================================

# Example fingerprint format:
# backend/elysia/api/utils/config.py:generic-api-key:127

# To add a false positive:
# 1. Run: gitleaks protect --verbose --staged
# 2. Copy the "Fingerprint:" line from the output
# 3. Paste it below
# 4. Commit and try again
